criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Presence of type 2 DM;

          -  Have at least 6 months from diagnosis of DM;

          -  Presence of Diabetic Polyneuropathy;

          -  No history of plantar orthoses and orthopedic footwear use.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Active ulceration;

          -  Severe osteoarticular deformities;

          -  Presence of cognitive impairment;

          -  Gait with technical devices;

          -  Diagnosis of neurological pathology that can affect the gait pattern;

          -  Diagnosis of another pathology that can negatively influence the study: depression,
             the presence of uncontrolled cardiovascular diseases and active cancer.

          -  Surgical interventions on the spine and lower limbs, with less than 1 year of
             recovery.
